> Can you please inform me how you got the LittleStar 67 to show the Mk1-2's ASET interior for IVAs?

Sorry for the late reply...

In your ASET folder you need to create a folder title Super67\_InternalASET

In that folder you need to create a config with this and title it "Super67\_ASETinternal-patch.cfg":

@PART[super67]:HAS[@MODULE[RasterPropMonitorComputer]]:Final 

{ 

@MODULE[RasterPropMonitorComputer] 

{

storedStrings = v 0.1.1.0|13.07.2015| Mark 1-2 Pod |ADVANCED LANDING CAPSULE|FOR ORBITAL RENDEZVOUS|SQD002002-A1|MK1-2| SQUAD & A.S.E.T.

}

@title = Super 67 Little Star

@INTERNAL

{

@name = Super67\_ASETInternals

}

}

@PART[super67]:HAS[!MODULE[RasterPropMonitorComputer]]:Final 

{ 

MODULE

{

name = RasterPropMonitorComputer

storedStrings = v 0.1.1.0|13.07.2015| Mark 1-2 Pod |ADVANCED LANDING CAPSULE|FOR ORBITAL RENDEZVOUS|SQD002002-A1|MK1-2| SQUAD & A.S.E.T.

}

@title = Super 67 Little Star

@INTERNAL

{

@name = Super67\_ASETInternals

}

}

Then you need to copy the "Spaces" folder from the Mk1-2\_InternalsASET folder.

Rename the .png's and replace "Mk1-2" with "Super67".

Finally, copy the config that is in the "Spaces" folder of the Mk1-2 ASET IVA.

Find where it says "name = Mk1-2\_ASETInternals" 

Just replace "Mk1-2" with "Super67"

That should do it!

